 (88,1,'2016-05-03 17:19:37','2016-05-03 17:19:37','The most thriving 24 hour coding event of IEEE, IEEEXtreme version 9.0 was organized by the student branch with the aid of Department of Computer Engineering. The event was accompanied with participation of 27 teams. All the team members eagerly participated as a result of pre coders session series held at the University to uplift the coding skills of participants. Every coder was determined to get there team to a better position in the ladder. But it was not an easy task. The problem definitions went tough to impossible sometimes. But with the efficient contribution of each member, some teams emerged with their ranks. The Student Branch facilitated the participants with coffee and refreshments through out the coding period. It seemed almost all of the teams enjoyed the 24 hours.\r\n\r\nIEEE associate members, Dr. Ruwan Ranaweera, Dr. Zyan Maraikkar, Dr. Samarakoon, Dr. Vijitha Herath and Mr. Sampath Degalla made a great contribution by being mentors through out the session. And also non academic staff of the Department of Computer Engineering also gave a great support in organizing the event.','IEEEXtreme','','inherit','closed','closed','','72-revision-v1','','','2016-05-03 17:19:37','2016-05-03 17:19:37','',72,'http://localhost/ieeeuop/2016/05/03/72-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
