/05/power_1-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"power_1\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">1.Wardenclyffe Tower: source: http://photos.wikimapia.org/p/00/02/68/43/77_full.jpg</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe inventions of the wireless power technologies may range from small day to day electronic devices to space docked power stations. The curiosity in your mind may simply add the question “How?”. Well, the transmission can be simply categorized into three concepts based on the distance of the transmission.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Short distance induction</li>\r\n 	<li>Moderate distance (Resonance)</li>\r\n 	<li>Long distance</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe simplest and the most fundamental wireless power transmission method of them all is the induction. An electrical transformer is a common example where the power transmission takes place by induction. The wireless mobile chargers you use today are a product of the induction research carried out throughout years. The device use coils to create a magnetic field where the receivers contain compatible coils to receive the transmission. While the short distance mutual induction is good way of charging up devices it cannot be used for long-range transmissions.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-99 aligncenter\" src=\"http://localhost/ieeeuop/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/power_2-300x170.jpg\" alt=\"power_2\" width=\"300\" height=\"170\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">2.wireless mobile chargers.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"> source :http://2.bp.blogspot.com/kw9uCANCSK8/TqBZ8LtbpeI/AAAAAAAAAGg/U8vsWESfXm0/s1600/powermat.jpg</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe moderate distance power transmission uses a far more advanced technique rather than just using mutual induction. If we were to use only induction, we would need a large powerful magnetic field to transfer the power. Developing a large magnetic field requires a lot of energy, and that’s where Tesla’s theories of resonance come into the action. The resonant frequency of an object is the frequency at which it naturally vibrates. You may have simply experienced the pendulum experiments where the energy transfer between two pendulums is maximum at their resonant frequencies. We can make power transmission more efficient by using the same resonant frequency for both transmitter and receiver coils thus making the electromagnetic fields around the coils resonate at the same frequency. The resonating coils act like a tunnel of transmission for the electricity travelling along an electromagnetic wave.\r\n\r\nSince the electromagnetic waves are tunneled, they wouldn’t disrupt other electronic devices within the range nor would the energy be dissipated through air. The electricity is transmitted through evanescent waves, which carry no energy. According to this, one transmitting station will be able to send electricity to several receiving coils although the system is still under research and not commercially used we can expect wireless power transmission towers in near future. The resonant power transmitting system makes it possible to transfer electrical power anywhere.\r\n\r\nLike it or not, the resonant inductive coupling is good for medium distances. The long distance wireless power involves advanced technology that can transmit energy over a span of miles. The electric power is converted into microwave power and the microwaves are directed to a rectifying antenna where the microwaves energy is extracted back from the receiving antennas. This microwave transmission has proved more efficient with conversion efficiencies exceeding 95%.\r\n\r\nThe most recent remarkable and significant research of the wireless power comes with the space bases solar power. In May 2015, Japan Aero Exploration Agency (JAXA) and Mitsubishi cooperation demonstrated their projects on long range wireless power transmission. Their transmission system is a part of a space based solar power collector where we can collect solar power directly from the space where the sun is always shining and effects of weather are different from that in the earth. The active role of wireless power involves in transmitting the collected energy from a space collector satellite to a station back in earth. On March 2015, JAXA was able to transmit 1.8Kilowatts of power over 55 meters with pinpoint accuracy using microwaves. Mitsubishi o the other hand managed to send 10 Kilowatts of power over a range of 500meteres. These research teams were able to transmit the power with an efficiency of 80%, JAXA is planning to further develop the system and test it in space by 2018. They have plans to have a 200MW solar power collector satellite by 2028.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-100 aligncenter\" src=\"http://localhost/ieeeuop/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/power_3-300x238.jpg\" alt=\"power_3\" width=\"300\" height=\"238\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">3.Space based solar power station. Source:http://www.mi2g.com/images/ssp.jpg</p>\r\nIf the plans go well, the space based power industry will kick off somewhere around 2030’s. With the rapidly developing wireless power transmission, the day where you can go out anywhere and light a bulb in your palm may be not far. The vast demand of power and the scarcity of energy resources is a major upcoming crisis. But, the wireless power has enlightened our hopes and paved way for a better future.\r\n\r\nWritten by,\r\n\r\nChathuska Pasindu Perera\r\n\r\n2<sup>nd</sup> year student\r\n\r\nDepartment of Electrical &amp; Electronic Engineering\r\n\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:Chatuska@gmail.com\">Chatuska@gmail.com</a>','Wireless Power For a Better Future','','inherit','closed','closed','','97-revision-v1','','','2016-05-04 18:21:19','2016-05-04 18:21:19','',97,'http://localhost/ieeeuop/2016/05/04/97-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
