 (138,1,'2016-05-08 14:17:44','2016-05-08 14:17:44','<div id=\"article-actions\">\r\n<div class=\"module article-tools actionbar\">\r\n\r\nIn this paper design and implementation of an accurate positioning system in indoor environments for an Omni directional Robot and a <span class=\"snippet\">stereo</span> <span class=\"snippet\">vision</span> based depth estimation system is discussed. The positioning system which is robust for wheel slip and jerky motion was implemented fusing odometry, Inertial Navigation System (INS) and magnetic compass based measurements. The <span class=\"snippet\">vision</span> system was implemented using two off the shelf web cameras. Here, Semi-Global Block Matching (SGBM) method was further developed considering multiple realizations of the same scenery to increase the accuracy of the depth estimation.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/xpl/articleDetails.jsp?arnumber=7399031&amp;queryText=iciis%202015%20stereo%20vision&amp;newsearch=true\">http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/xpl/articleDetails.jsp?arnumber=7399031&amp;queryText=iciis%202015%20stereo%20vision&amp;newsearch=true</a>\r\n\r\nAuthors:\r\n\r\nA. H. A. D. Abeysekara\r\nD. P. Liyanage ; W. R. C. B. S. Welikala ; G. M. R. I. Godaliyadda ; M. P. B. Eakanayake ; J. V. Wijayakulasooriya\r\nDepartment of Electrical and Electronic Engineering, University of Peradeniya, Sri Lanka\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Depth map generation for a reconnaissance robot via sensor fusion','','inherit','closed','closed','','137-revision-v1','','','2016-05-08 14:17:44','2016-05-08 14:17:44','',137,'http://localhost/ieeeuop/2016/05/08/137-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
