 (159,1,'2016-05-09 05:16:59','2016-05-09 05:16:59','Authors: <a href=\"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/search/searchresult.jsp?searchWithin=%22Authors%22:.QT.N.%20R.%20W.%20W.%20M.%20R.%20D%20Wickramasingha.QT.&amp;newsearch=true\">R. W. W. M. R. D Wickramasingha</a> ; Department of Computer Engineering, University of Peradeniya, Sri Lanka ; <a href=\"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/search/searchresult.jsp?searchWithin=%22Authors%22:.QT.H.%20B.%20R.%20A.%20K.%20R.%20A.%20M%20Keerawella.QT.&amp;newsearch=true\">H. B. R. A. K. R. A. M Keerawella</a> ; <a href=\"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/search/searchresult.jsp?searchWithin=%22Authors%22:.QT.S.%20A.%20N%20Samarasinghe.QT.&amp;newsearch=true\">S. A. N Samarasinghe</a> ; <a href=\"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/search/searchresult.jsp?searchWithin=%22Authors%22:.QT.R.%20G.%20Ragel.QT.&amp;newsearch=true\">R. G. Ragel</a>\n\nCompletely Automated Public Turing test to tell Computers and Humans Apart (CAPTCHA) is a challenge-response system test used on the web, designed to differentiate humans from automated computer systems. Most of the widely used CAPTCHA systems are designed with desktop users in mind hence lack the native look and feel when they are used on mobile devices. The reason is the way people interact with desktop/laptop computer using mouse and keyboard is different from the way they interact with mobile devices using touch and other gestures. Also, the screen size and the dimension of the viewing display plays a role in the interaction. Here, we present a novel CAPTCHA system designed for mobile devices and results of the usability study that we conducted with an implementation of the same. This CAPTCHA system is composed of multipart image reconstruction and orientation identification. Although, this is an intuitive task for humans, it is very hard to automate using a computer system. The main advantages of our system over traditional systems are native mobile look and feel, language/culture independent, and gesture-based interaction.\n\n<strong>Published in: </strong><a href=\"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/xpl/mostRecentIssue.jsp?punumber=7391617\">2015 IEEE 10th International Conference on Industrial and Information Systems (ICIIS)</a>\n\n<strong> IEEE Xplore link:<u>  </u></strong><a href=\"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/xpl/articleDetails.jsp?arnumber=7398984&amp;queryText=iciis%202015&amp;refinements=4224982482&amp;refinements=4224981563&amp;refinements=4224982573&amp;refinements=4224983845\">http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/xpl/articleDetails.jsp?arnumber=7398984&amp;queryText=iciis%202015&amp;refinements=4224982482&amp;refinements=4224981563&amp;refinements=4224982573&amp;refinements=4224983845</a>\n\n&nbsp;','RotateCAPTCHA a novel interactive CAPTCHA design targeting mobile devices','','inherit','closed','closed','','150-autosave-v1','','','2016-05-09 05:16:59','2016-05-09 05:16:59','',150,'http://localhost/ieeeuop/2016/05/09/150-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
 (160,1,'2016-05-09 05:14:54','2016-05-09 05:14:54','Authors: <a href=\"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/search/searchresult.jsp?searchWithin=%22Authors%22:.QT.Hasindu%20Gamaarachchi.QT.&amp;newsearch=true\">Hasindu Gamaarachchi</a> ;\r\nDepartment of Computer Engineering, University of Peradeniya, Sri Lanka ; <a href=\"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/search/searchresult.jsp?searchWithin=%22Authors%22:.QT.Harsha%20Ganegoda.QT.&amp;newsearch=true\">Harsha Ganegoda</a> ; <a href=\"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/search/searchresult.jsp?searchWithin=%22Authors%22:.QT.Roshan%20Ragel.QT.&amp;newsearch=true\">Roshan Ragel</a>\r\n\r\nCorrelation Power Analysis (CPA) based Side Channel Attack (SCA) is a popular modern cryptanalysis typically used by adversaries in embedded devices to break their secret keys. CPA uses the correlation between the power consumption of the cryptosystem and the computation performed to derive the secret key. Proposing countermeasures against such attacks require a testbed for implementation and verification. Although, a large number of such attacks and countermeasures are proposed in the literature, building of testbeds are still not presented properly. Therefore, researchers starting to work on CPA have to spend an enormous amount of time for building and debugging such testbeds. Also, a few testbeds presented in the literature have their limitations. In this paper, we present an A to Z guide for preparing a CPA testbed that also addresses the shortcomings of the existing testbeds in the literature.\r\n\r\n<strong>Published in: </strong><a href=\"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/xpl/mostRecentIssue.jsp?punumber=7391617\">2015 IEEE 10th International Conference on Industrial and Information Systems (ICIIS) </a>\r\n\r\n<strong>IEEE Xplore link: </strong><a href=\"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/xpl/articleDetails.jsp?arnumber=7399063&amp;queryText=iciis%202015&amp;refinements=4224982482&amp;refinements=4224981563&amp;refinements=4224982573&amp;refinements=4224983845\">http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/xpl/articleDetails.jsp?arnumber=7399063&amp;queryText=iciis%202015&amp;refinements=4224982482&amp;refinements=4224981563&amp;refinements=4224982573&amp;refinements=4224983845</a>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-158\" src=\"http://localhost/ieeeuop/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/27fe696-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"27fe696\" width=\"99\" height=\"99\" />\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/search/searchresult.jsp?searchWithin=%22Authors%22:.QT.Hasindu%20Gamaarachchi.QT.&amp;newsearch=true\">Hasindu Gamaarachchi</a>\r\nLinkedIn: <a href=\"https://lk.linkedin.com/in/hasindugamaarachchi\">https://lk.linkedin.com/in/hasindugamaarachchi</a>','The A to Z of building a testbed for Power Analysis attacks','','inherit','closed','closed','','148-revision-v1','','','2016-05-09 05:14:54','2016-05-09 05:14:54','',148,'http://localhost/ieeeuop/2016/05/09/148-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
